    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>white long grain rice </strong>and <strong>cauliflower rice</strong> to a pot with a lid with 110ml [<span class=\"text-purple\">175ml</span>] [<span class=\"text-danger\">225ml</span>] cold water and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-and-black-bean-stir-fry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and cut your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong> into quarters, then separate the wedges so you end up with a pile of onion petals</p><p>Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Boil half a kettle</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-and-black-bean-stir-fry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>pork mince</strong> (remove the paper if required!)<strong> </strong>to the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and roughly break it up with a wooden spoon so you're left with bite-sized pieces</p><p>Cook for 4-5 min turning once halfway until browned all over</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-and-black-bean-stir-fry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the pork is browning, trim your <strong>green beans</strong>, then chop into bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-and-black-bean-stir-fry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your<strong> black bean paste </strong>in 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml] </span><strong>boiled</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>water </strong>with your <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>toasted sesame oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>sugar </strong>\u2013 this is your<strong> black bean stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-and-black-bean-stir-fry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the pork is beginning to brown, add the <strong>onion petals</strong> and <strong>chopped green beans </strong>to the pan with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>flour</strong> and mix it all together</p><p>Cook for 2-3 min, stirring occasionally, until the onion petals are starting to soften</p><p>Once slightly softened, add the <strong>sliced garlic</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-and-black-bean-stir-fry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>black bean stock </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Cook for a final 4-5 min or until the sauce has thickened and the pork mince is cooked through (no pink meat!)<strong> </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>pork & black bean stir-fry</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/pork-and-black-bean-stir-fry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> pork & black bean stir-fry</strong> with the <strong>cooked cauliflower rice</strong> to the side</p><p>Tip: For fancy presentation, press the rice into a small bowl and turn out</p><p>Season with a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
